GiRS","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recIrbQVTdfJc0cBM","ref":"Gen.25.1","text":"Then again Abraham took a wife, and her name was Keturah.","year":-1853},{"id":"recD653dcCCe7tlL5","ref":"Gen.25.2","text":"And she bare him Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah.","year":-1852},{"id":"rec1kNAE5GK2YJBvl","ref":"Gen.25.3","text":"And Jokshan begat Sheba, and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim, and Letushim, and Leummim.","year":-1824},{"id":"recM0DIc9X9mQEoFC","ref":"Gen.25.4","text":"And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Hanoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.","year":-1804},{"id":"recpbybp2PfpNnxLm","ref":"Gen.25.5","text":"And Abraham gave all that he had unto Isaac.","year":-1829},{"id":"recPwtsljxiFCSFKO","ref":"Gen.25.6","text":"But unto the sons of the concubines, which Abraham had, Abraham gave gifts, and sent them away from Isaac his son, while he yet lived, eastward, unto the east country.","year":-1829},{"id":"recIVXkKlPw1Jvuul","ref":"Gen.25.7","text":"And these are the days of the years of Abraham’s life which he lived, an hundred threescore and fifteen years.","year":-1821},{"id":"recEpjIweIdGcHYS0","ref":"Gen.25.8","text":"Then Abraham gave up the ghost, and died in a good old age, an old man, and full of years; and was gathered to his people.","year":-1821}]}
